==English==

===Etymology===
[[Image:ClemensXI.jpg|thumb|right|A coin.]]
French ''[[coin#French|coin]]'' (corner, die for stamping, wedge), confer English ''[[quoin]]''. From Latin ''[[cuneus]]'' ((troops in) wedge (formation)).

